Setup Device Alerts
2015-05-14 17:48
Getting Started
To change the triggers for device alerts that appear on the homepage:<br><br>1. Go the <b>Setting</b> page&nbsp;<br><br>2. Change the values on the following fields:<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<label class="integer required control-label control-label" for="settings_unresponsive_device_days" style="display: inline-block; max-width: 100%; margin-bottom: 5px; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 2px; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><i>Days without checkins until a device is marked as unresponsive<br></i>﻿<br>This setting decides after how long of the device not connecting to Cellabus's servers, the device should be market as unresponsive. By default it's 7 days.<br><br><i>﻿</i><span style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 20px;"><i>Minimum storage capacity percent until warning is shown<br></i></span><br>Decides at what device storage level, a device is marked as having low storage capacity. By default it's 10%.<br><br><i>﻿</i><span style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 20px;"><i>Minimum battery level percent until warning is shown<br></i></span><br>Decides at what battery level a device is marked as having low battery. By default it's 20%.<br></label><div></div><div><label class="integer required control-label control-label" for="settings_unresponsive_device_days" style="display: inline-block; max-width: 100%; margin-bottom: 5px; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 2px; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></label></div>
